  "timeframe": "15m",
  "market_context": "ETH on the 15-minute is in a consolidation after rallying near 26280. The analyst is deciding whether price will manipulate higher to reverse, or break the range to the downside and continue lower.",
  "key_observation": "After the consolidation breakout to the downside, price retraced higher into a point of interest (highlighted bearish FVG/zone) and produced a clean closure through it, confirming the continuation and a protected high to trade lower.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Frame the consolidation and ask whether price will manipulate the range to trade higher or break down.",
    "Identify the requirement for trading a breakout of a range: wait for a continuation after the break.",
    "Watch price trade higher back into a point of interest (FVG zone) after the initial breakdown.",
    "Confirm a clean closure through that point of interest, establishing a protected high that should hold.",
    "Re-evaluate the next leg: a smaller consolidation forms internally, so look for either manipulation of the range to continue lower or a break out higher.",
    "Observe a candle three closure that breaks lower, taking a short-term low, and note that another continuation is required before trading further lower."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "To trade a consolidation breakout, do not chase the initial break — wait for price to retrace into a point of interest and produce a continuation closure that forms a protected high/low, then trade in the breakout direction.",
